            "content": {
                "raw": "I guess I didn't appreciate that parallelism will only work when importing from `yt.mods`.  Is that the case or am I misreading things?\n\nIf so it's definitely worth thinking about how to make it work if I want to avoid using `yt.mods`.  Taking a look at everything else that's handled by `yt.mods` after, I think parallelism is the only one that we really can't live without in an `import yt` future.",
                "html": "<p>I guess I didn't appreciate that parallelism will only work when importing from <code>yt.mods</code>.  Is that the case or am I misreading things?</p>\n<p>If so it's definitely worth thinking about how to make it work if I want to avoid using <code>yt.mods</code>.  Taking a look at everything else that's handled by <code>yt.mods</code> after, I think parallelism is the only one that we really can't live without in an <code>import yt</code> future.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
