            "content": {
                "raw": "@ngoldbaum yes, that's actually the case, and it's intentional.  The idea was that importing `yt` will be more like treating yt as a library, and we avoid as many side effects as possible.  Importing `yt.mods` signals that it's okay to have side effects, which in this case is parallelism.",
                "html": "<p><a href=\"/ngoldbaum/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@ngoldbaum\" class=\"mention\">Nathan Goldbaum</a> yes, that's actually the case, and it's intentional.  The idea was that importing <code>yt</code> will be more like treating yt as a library, and we avoid as many side effects as possible.  Importing <code>yt.mods</code> signals that it's okay to have side effects, which in this case is parallelism.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
