            "content": {
                "raw": "To be honest, I have absolutely zero problem with ditching most/all of this PR -- I don't mind having a ``yt.mods`` that gets imported, that we use to set up side-effects, etc etc.  I implemented it in such a way so that we could have the use case of yt-as-just-a-library (full of data objects and the like) and yt-as-a-sort-of-application, where it'll do things like set up logging, create MPI communicators, blah blah.  Maybe we should talk about it on the list?",
                "html": "<p>To be honest, I have absolutely zero problem with ditching most/all of this PR -- I don't mind having a <code>yt.mods</code> that gets imported, that we use to set up side-effects, etc etc.  I implemented it in such a way so that we could have the use case of yt-as-just-a-library (full of data objects and the like) and yt-as-a-sort-of-application, where it'll do things like set up logging, create MPI communicators, blah blah.  Maybe we should talk about it on the list?</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
